Unrest engulfed Iran in late December after a massive protest against the Khamenei regime was handled with muscle power. Nearly 3,000 lives were lost during the violent crackdown on protestors in the last two weeks.

The situation escalated beyond the borders after Trump said that he was sending help to anti-regime protestors. The situation appears to return to normal as Trump drops his aggressive stance against Iran.

9,000 Indian nationals are currently present in Iran, hence India is observing situation closely.


